Axis Says Disasters Cost Up to $105 Million, Led by U.S. Storms

-- B y   B r o o k e   S u t h e r l a n d
-- 
2011-07-14T13:00:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/axis-says-disasters-cost-up-to-105-million-led-by-u-s-storms.html
Axis Capital Holdings Ltd. (AXS) , the
Bermuda-based insurer, said second-quarter catastrophes cost the
firm $90 million to $105 million after tax.  The total includes as much as $70 million from U.S. storms
in April and May, the insurer said today in a statement
distributed by  Business Wire .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brooke Sutherland in New York at 
 Bsutherland5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  